  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Securing decent work in tropical fruit export production</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Most tropical fruits are grown by workers with low wages and poor working conditions. It can also be extremely dangerous because of the chemicals used and the highly demanding physical work. Governments keen to receive foreign investment and generate jobs often overlook national legislation on labour standards; and workers especially women are often unaware of or unable to realise their rights. This project will work with unions to raise awareness of their members and other workers about their rights, and to negotiate effectively for living wages and improved conditions. Consumer awareness will be raised to keep the pressure on the industry to change its behaviour and respect workers&#x2019; rights.</narrative>
  </description>
